Document Controller
Confidential Company - ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/05 13:36:13
Ref. JB3016315
Job Description
Job Scope
Responsible for managing company’s documents while also ensuring their accuracy, quality and integrity.
Organize and maintain documents, adhering to the company's document lifecycle procedures.
Main Duties and Responsibilities
Coordinate all activities related to the Document Control procedure, including technical documents, drawings and commercial correspondence.
Input document data into the standard register ensuring that the information is accurate and up to date.
Generate the various document control reports as required
Typing of site documents and follow up of ll the site needs.
Make sure that controlled copies of latest approved documents and drawings are given to the appropriate staff, subcontractors and suppliers as applicable.
Maintain updated records of all approved documents and drawings and their distribution clearly.
Maintain the documents and drawings in the Document Control Office under safe custody without any damage or deterioration with easy traceability
Maintain the files and control logs as required by the project and follow up on weekly status.
Skills
Education
High School Diploma. Bachelor degree is highly appreciated
Experience
3 to 4 years’ experience in a similar job function
